         <abstract>
            <p>
               Using the basis reduction algorithm of A. K. Lenstra, H. W. Lenstra, Jr. and L. Lovász [8] and an idea of Buchmann [4], we describe a method for computing maximal systems of independent units in arbitrary number fields. The tables in the supplements section display such systems for the fields $\mathbf{Q}(\sqrt[n]{D})$ where $6 \leq n \leq 11$. 
            </p>
